## The Week at a Glance

- 🔴 **Active supply-chain attacks stealing cloud credentials** — Two live campaigns (dependency confusion and typosquatted npm packages) are actively targeting developer and build environments to steal credentials for GitHub, AWS, Kubernetes, and other platforms. Organizations with software development or CI/CD pipelines face immediate risk of credential theft and downstream breach.
- 🔴 **On-premises Exchange Server XSS vulnerability (CVE-2026-42897)** — A disclosed vulnerability in Exchange Outlook Web Access allows arbitrary JavaScript execution when a user opens a crafted email. Any organization still running Exchange Server 2016, 2019, or Subscription Edition must apply the published mitigation immediately; Exchange Online is not affected.
- 🟡 **Teams Live Events retirement on June 30, 2026** — Scheduling of Teams Live Events ends in four weeks. Organizations using live events for town halls, all-hands meetings, or external broadcasts must migrate to the new Teams events experience before that date or lose the ability to schedule new events.
- 🟢 **AI agent governance tooling now generally available** — Microsoft Agent 365, Copilot Studio computer-using agents, and Entra identity controls for agents all reached general availability this period. Organizations deploying AI agents now have production-grade governance tools at their disposal; awareness and adoption planning is warranted.

*Sources: [Microsoft Security Blog — Mini Shai-Hulud](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/05/20/mini-shai-hulud-compromised-antv-npm-packages-enable-ci-cd-credential-theft/) · [Microsoft Security Blog — Dependency Confusion](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/05/29/33-malicious-npm-packages-abuse-dependency-confusion-profile-developer-environments/) · [Exchange Team Blog — CVE-2026-42897](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/addressing-exchange-server-may-2026-vulnerability-cve-2026-42897/ba-p/4518498) · [Teams Blog — Live Events Retirement](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-teams-blog/retiring-teams-live-events-the-next-chapter-for-events-at-scale/ba-p/4486465)*

