| **[CVE-2026-42897: Exchange Server OWA JavaScript injection](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/addressing-exchange-server-may-2026-vulnerability-cve-2026-42897/ba-p/4518498)** | Affects all on-premises Exchange Server versions (2016, 2019, SE). A crafted email opened in OWA can execute attacker JavaScript in the user's browser, enabling session hijacking or credential theft. Exchange Online is NOT affected. | HIPAA (email system integrity), CMMC, NIST CSF (Respond), cyber insurance patching requirements | **Immediate — apply published mitigation** |
